OL,3,CScottish government spends #200m on IT
OL,4,Cconsultants for farming payments
OL,6,FMore than #200m has been spent by the
OL,7,FScottish government on external
OL,8,Fconsultants to help run a subsidy
OL,9,Fsystem for farmers, Representing
OL,10,FBorder has learned.
OL,12,FOfficial figures show that on average
OL,13,Fmore than #20m has been paid out each
OL,14,Fyear to companies to advise and
OL,15,Fadminister agricultural support
OL,16,Fpayments over the last nine years.
OL,18,FThe total spend is just over #203m
OL,19,Fsince 2016, the vast majority of which
OL,20,Fwent to three external companies.
